ssemblies. It also provides earth moving and construction components, including pins, side cutter, teeth, bushes, and fasteners; and propeller shaft components, such as leaf spring, full yoke, rear teeth, cross holder, coupling flange, half yoke, water pump assy, UJ cross, tie rod end and drag link kits, wheel spanners, and jack pod, as well as offers designing solutions for product performance and quality improvement. The company operates in India, the United Kingdom, Germany, Holland, Malaysia, Saudi Arabia, Iran, the United Arab Emirates, the United States, Morocco, Egypt, the Philippines, Afghanistan, Singapore, Bahrain, Kuwait, and Kenya. The company was formerly known as Gurmukh Singh & Sons Auto Parts Private Limited and changed its name to G.S. Auto International Limited in 1985. G.S. Auto International Limited was founded in 1938 and is based in Ludhiana, India."}}